docs.snippet: Last week's trading in the foreign exchanges was as small in volume and narrow in rate fluctuations as in the preceding week. About all that went on were routine requirements. The value of the dollar, measured by the quotation for the French franc,...
docs.lead_paragraph: Last week's trading in the foreign exchanges was as small in volume and narrow in rate fluctuations as in the preceding week. About all that went on were routine requirements. The value of the dollar, measured by the quotation for the French franc, was steady throughout, holding to a high premium of 0.6 cent, and a low and final of 0.5, unchanged from the previous week. Range a year ago was 71.30 @ 68.73 cents.
